data.content:
Here's the minimal program (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Jane", 30);
var json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase
});
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

Output: `{"name":"Jane","age":30}`

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` in the serializer options — it converts `Name` → `name` and `Age` → `age`. No extra NuGet packages needed; `System.Text.Json` is built into .NET 8.
